name: scljet-sql-concat
description: SclJet SQL || string concatenation — NULL-propagating, numeric coercion, with functions and in WHERE; matches reference sqlite3
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet SQL `||` string concatenation

`a || b` joins the text forms of both operands; a NULL operand makes the whole result NULL, and a
numeric operand is coerced to its text form (`id || ':' || first`, `first || age`). It chains, composes
with scalar functions (`UPPER(first) || '-' || LOWER(last)`), and works in `WHERE`. Every result is
byte-identical to reference sqlite3 running the same SQL on the same file (verified out-of-band);
locked here across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlNull, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "people", "CREATE TABLE people(id INTEGER, first TEXT, last TEXT, age INTEGER)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("John"), SqlText("Smith"), SqlInteger(30L)),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("jane"), SqlText("Doe"), SqlInteger(25L)),
       List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlText("Bob"), SqlNull, SqlInteger(40L)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db) =>
    show(db, "SELECT id, first || ' ' || last FROM people")
    show(db, "SELECT id || ':' || first FROM people")
    show(db, "SELECT first || age FROM people")
    show(db, "SELECT UPPER(first) || '-' || LOWER(last) FROM people")
    show(db, "SELECT first || COALESCE(last, '?') FROM people")
    show(db, "SELECT id FROM people WHERE first || last = 'JohnSmith'")
```
